'''Lewis Martin''' (born 19 August 2004) is an English professional [[rugby league]] footballer who plays as a {{rlp|wg}}er for [[Hull F.C.]] in the [[Super League]].

Martin initially planned to become a [[association football|footballer]] and was signed to [[Hull City A.F.C.]] at the age of nine. After being released by the club at age 15, he switched to rugby league and was offered a scholarship by [[Hull F.C.]]<ref>{{cite news |last=Shaw |first=Matthew |url=https://www.hulldailymail.co.uk/sport/rugby-league/who-lewis-martin-hull-fc-9102059 |title=Who is Lewis Martin? Hull FC winger who chose rugby league after Hull City rejection |work=Hull Daily Mail |date=15 February 2024 |access-date=4 April 2025}}</ref>

In 2023 he made his Hull début in the [[Super League]] against [[St Helens R.F.C.|St Helens]] in a 30-12 loss scoring a try.<ref>{{cite news |title=Super League: St Helens 30-12 Hull FC - Saints win but miss out on place in top two |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/rugby-league/66870850 |work=BBC Sport |date=22 September 2023 |access-date=1 April 2025}}</ref>

Martin was the top scorer for Hull F.C. in the 2024 season, scoring 9 tries.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Costello |first1=Tim |title=Hull F.C. 2024 Season |url=https://www.rugbyleagueproject.org/seasons/super-league-2024/hull-fc/summary.html |website=Rugby League Project |access-date=2 April 2025}}</ref>

In 2025, Hull F.C. drew [[Wigan Warriors]] in the round of 16 of the [[Challenge Cup]]. Martin scored a hat-trick to help win the game.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Tomlinson |first1=Daniel |title=Lewis Martin's Hull FC write-off message as winger reflects on winning try and 'unreal' win |url=https://www.hulldailymail.co.uk/sport/rugby-league/lewis-martins-coming-age-moment-10027422 |work=Hull Daily Mail |access-date=2 April 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Tomlinson |first1=Daniel |title=Hull FC produce Challenge Cup miracle to defeat Wigan with Lewis Martin scoring hat-trick|url=https://www.hulldailymail.co.uk/sport/rugby-league/match-reports/hull-fc-produce-challenge-cup-10027418 |work=Hull Daily Mail |access-date=1 April 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Match Report: Wigan Warriors 22-26 Hull FC |date=15 March 2025 |url=https://www.hullfc.com/blog/2025/03/15/match-report-wigan-warriors-22-26-hull-fc/ |publisher=Hull F.C. |access-date=2 April 2025}}</ref>

